(42, 8, 14, 62, 2, 15, 17, 'cares and riches and pleasures of this life', 'Connection of Worldly Distractions', 'Both passages emphasize the dangers of worldly cares and desires that hinder spiritual growth. Luke 8:14 mentions being ''choked with cares and riches,'' while 1 John 2:15-17 warns against ''the things that are in the world.''', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 14, 54, 6, 9, 10, 'choked with cares and riches', 'Connection of Wealth and Spiritual Fruitfulness', 'Both passages emphasize the dangers of wealth and worldly pleasures, illustrating how they can hinder spiritual growth and lead to destruction. The thorns in Luke represent distractions that choke spiritual fruitfulness, while 1 Timothy warns of the temptations and sorrows associated with the love of money.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 14, 54, 6, 17, 17, 'riches and pleasures of this life', 'Connection of Wealth and Spiritual Fruitfulness', 'Both passages emphasize the dangers of wealth and its potential to distract from spiritual growth. Luke warns that cares and riches choke spiritual fruitfulness, while Timothy advises against trusting in uncertain riches.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 14, 40, 6, 24, 25, 'cares and riches', 'Connection of Material Concerns', 'Both passages emphasize the dangers of being consumed by worldly concerns, such as ''cares and riches'' in Luke and ''thought for your life'' in Matthew. They highlight the conflict between serving God and being distracted by materialism.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
