(42, 8, 14, 42, 21, 34, 34, NULL, 'Connection of Life''s Cares', 'Both passages emphasize the dangers of being consumed by the cares of life, which can hinder spiritual growth and awareness. The focus on worldly distractions in both verses highlights a common theme of vigilance against such influences.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 15, 58, 10, 36, 36, 'bring forth fruit with patience', 'Patience in Faithfulness', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of patience in the process of spiritual growth and fulfillment. Luke highlights that those with a good heart bring forth fruit with patience, while Hebrews stresses the need for patience after doing God''s will to receive the promise.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 15, 48, 5, 22, 26, 'bring forth fruit with patience', 'Connection of Spiritual Fruit', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of producing fruit as a result of a genuine response to God''s word and the Spirit. Luke highlights the importance of a good heart that bears fruit, while Galatians lists the specific fruits of the Spirit that believers should exhibit.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 15, 51, 1, 10, 10, 'bring forth fruit with patience', 'Fruitfulness in Good Works', 'Both passages emphasize being fruitful in good works. Luke highlights the importance of keeping the word with a good heart, while Colossians encourages walking worthy of the Lord and being fruitful in every good work.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
